---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const socialLinks = [
  { name: "GitHub", url: "https://github.com/olivergilan" },
  { name: "LinkedIn", url: "https://linkedin.com/in/oliver-gilan/" },
  { name: "Twitter", url: "https://twitter.com/olvrgln" },
];
---

<BaseLayout description="A public slice of my personal journal">
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <strong class="font-semibold">Hello, this site is a public slice of my personal journal</strong> where
      I share what I'm interested in and what I've learned â€” usually about engineering,
      business, and life. A few of the problems I'm currently spending a lot of time
      thinking about are the ability (or lack thereof) to create great software at
      scale, creating artificial organs, and optimizing my personal health.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
      My long-form writing is posted on my <a href="/blog/">blog</a> while my thoughts
      that aren't fleshed out enough for a full entry are posted as a <a href="/stream/">stream</a> of consciousness.
      I'm currently compiling a list of the <a href="/books/">100 books</a> that I would read over and over again
      and I maintain a <a href="/blogroll/">blogroll</a> of writings and websites I love to read.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
      You can email me at <em>blog (at) olivergilan.com</em> or reach me at the following links:
    </p>

    <ul class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4 list-none p-0">
      {
        socialLinks.map((link) => (
          <li>
            <a
              href={link.url}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-lg"
            >
              {link.name}
            </a>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ul>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
